cafes.name: The Toebean Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 20 Walnut Ave SW, Roanoke, VA 24016, USA

text.text: I went to the opening today and it was FANTASTIC. The cafe is light, airy, so welcoming but also cozy at the same time. The cats were in the best rooms, it was almost as good as forever homes. They had everything cats could ever want. The coffee was fabulous - I had a delightful mocha and the pastries looked absolutely divine. I‚Äôd stop by there just to get coffee, even without the incentive of adorable cats!!  It is a great place to take your laptop and do some work in a chill fun environment.  The owners were both there and they were awesome - they‚Äôre vet techs as well so I can‚Äôt ever imagine a cat cafe in better hands!!   I bought gift certificates for some friends - it‚Äôs the perfect gift and totally unique!!!

I stopped by the new cat cafe and had such a great time! Even though we didn‚Äôt get to hang out with the cats because we didn‚Äôt have a reservation, the cafe itself is super cute with all the cat-themed decor. My coffee was delicious too! I love that they‚Äôre all about helping cats find homes through local shelters! Definitely a place worth supporting, and I‚Äôll make sure to book ahead next time!

The Toebean Cat Cafe offers a truly unique experience. The environment is filled with light and warmth, creating a cozy atmosphere all throughout. The cats are so loving and sweet, making it the perfect place to spend a morning or afternoon. The staff are helpful and kind, and it's clear that owners care deeply about these animals. Overall, it was a joyful experience. Plus, the coffee was absolutely delicious!

cafes.name: Mount Purrnon Cat Caf√© + Wine Bar
cafes.address: 109 S Alfred St, Alexandria, VA 22314, USA

text.text: The cafe is such a great addition to the cat space, and it‚Äôs clear that the cats are well loved and taken care of. Some cats are seniors and just living out their last years in a bright, clean, lovely space, and others are much younger who are eager to make friends! The staff genuinely care about the cats and their care. Please stop by, support them and adopt!

MOUNT PURRNON CAT CAFE & WINE BAR has become a must-do for out of town kiddos visiting Northern Virginia, if you love cats and you love kiddies.

Mount Purrnon is located on Alfred Street just off King Street, the main 'drag' in Old Town Alexandria so everywhere you turn you are walking in historic footsteps. Parking is on the street. Payment is fed in to free standing rectangles. The receipt is placed on your car dashboard.

Mount Purrnon is a healthy walk towards the water with your back to the Metro. If you are lucky, you can catch Old Town's free trolley, a fun thing kids of all ages love to do. The trolley will land you near enough to the cafe allowing you to combine two kid fun events in one outing. ,

The Mount Purrnon Cafe is kitty corner to a vintage shop, around the cornerdown the street from Sephora and up the street from the amazing Torpedo Factory.

Entering Mount Purrnon Cat Cafe + Wine Bar, you enter the most delightful gift shop filled with cat 'stuff' of all types, high end, crafty and lower priced fun stuff, all benefiting the charity housed in this historic house once upon a time someone, maybe, infamous in history lived there, after all, ghosts of America's fathers still live there, technically.

Friendly volunteers sit waiting to take payment for adults, kids, lunch if you choose and the length of time your visit to last- 1/2 hour, an hour. I once met a young woman who pretty much spent all day there. She said she found inner peace.

Mount Purrnon profiles its current residents on the wall in this room so you sorta have an idea which kitties you will be greeted by upstairs AND maybe even want to take home with you if you are in the market for a furrever friend.

The stairs are a bit steep heading up to the cattery. There are steps outside, too.

Before you head up, there is a downstairs eating place with a limited menu that includes out of this world cheese melt sandwich a finicky-as-a-cat four year old I know literally inhales this sandwich. There is a cat themed bathroom on the first floor. It's sort of a nice thing to do- eat first, fill your tummy then head up the stairs.

The photos speak for themselves. I wanted to take them all but, got a better offer, two kiddos who love love love coming here to Mount Purrnon Cafe. Thank you, yet again.

oh yeah, photos are copyright (c) Carrie Devorah and may not be used unless given permission by me, not by google or the cafe

We had a wonderful time at Mount Purrnon! The staff was so helpful in answering our questions and they were informative of the cats. This business is doing wonderful things to support cats in the area. Will definitely be back!

cafes.name: Cups and Claws Cat Cafe and Lounge
cafes.address: 10605 Jefferson Ave, Newport News, VA 23601, USA

text.text:
Got our big boy Rock from here :) had a great time petting all the kitties and feeding them treats. All the staff was friendly, incredibly helpful and very knowledgeable. Will definitely be going back
.
.
6 month update! Toast, (was Rock) is doing amazing! And his new kitty friends love him so much! Special shout out to cups and claws because he's so well socialized and is very friendly with new friends as well as critters.

Perfect for all cat lovers. As soon as I stepped through the door I was greeted with love from the kitties. The atmosphere was so cozy and the staff were so nice, and the owner was very helpful with starting the adoption process of one of their cats for me. I definitely recommend for anyone who loves cats and wants to just chill with them or anyone who is thinking about adopting one ‚ù§Ô∏è
I went to the 1980‚Äôs murder mystery event and I had so much fun! Everyone was so friendly and it was such a cozy and positive atmosphere!!! 10/10 recommend! (Plus the cutest kitties everywhere)!

I absolutely love coming here. The cats are rescues, and you come visit to help them socialize or if you're looking for a new family member since they're adoptable. They are all well taken care of! Noted that it's best to make a reservation online since spaces can fill up quickly.

My partner and I have been here several times over the past few months, and it was worth it every single visit!

Staff is incredible, friendly all around, and make the cafe feel super welcoming. The cats are always a delight, and Kittenpalooza is a great event to socialize the younger kitties!

Overall an amazing place, and I highly recommend this location to anyone looking to relax with some cats for a bit üêà‚Äç‚¨õ

A much need kitty time. So many Amzing  personalitys to play with. 2 got adopted while we were there. So happy they got a home together.  Thank you to the people who own and made this place possible.  I would be here every week if I lived hear.

Cutest place ever!!!! Today my mom took me and my 11 year old daughter here and we had a great experience. All the cats were adorable and super nice. I was impressed with how everything looked inside, nice and clean. They had some little bakery type stuff and teas and coffee. Such a cute idea. I'm glad we went. The girl who was working today was very kind and helpful.

Absolutely adorable place doing amazing things for animals.

We stopped in as a surprise for my teens.  We paid the $16 each for one hour in the rooms.  They have older cats and kittens separated into two rooms on either side of the cafe portion.  I sat in the middle and had a drink and cupcake while they went in.

Very nicely kept.  I had been worried about a smell, but it wasn't noticeable.

My kids spent time in each room loving and being loved on by the cats and kittens.  This is a very clever way of getting the cats ready to be adopted.

They have food for purchase, but all we got was a drink and cupcake for me which were well made and yummy.

Delicious treats and drinks accompany the opportunity to watch or interact with some very adorable, sweet kitties. All of which are adoptable! What a great spot to hang out and have a cup of coffee. üôÇ‚òïÔ∏èüêà

cafes.name: Catty Corner Cafe
cafes.address: 116 E Market St, Leesburg, VA 20176, USA

text.text: I love this place - the cats are so sweet and well taken care of. The staff is very nice and they usually will tell you about each cat too. The shop has a lot of unique gifts for cat lovers as well. Also the home made cookies are really good - I like the oatmeal cookie. üêæ

It was a good experience being here. I never thought there was a cat caf√© in US. I‚Äôve only been to one in Japan. The cats were very friendly and cute. It‚Äôs good that these cats are adoptable and rescues. I wish the area was bigger and more clean though. I‚Äôm saying this because I‚Äôve been to one in Japan and I didn‚Äôt smell any cat litter odor there so I bet there‚Äôs a way that this place can get better. I would go back here.

cute place! they have a drink station, baked cookies and a little shop downstairs, and upstairs is the actual kitty area. cats had lots of funny personalities hehe

just keep in mind it's in Old Town Leesburg, so parking can sometimes be annoying

cafes.name: Twisted Cat Tavern
cafes.address: 19332 Town Green Drive, Leesburg, VA 20176, USA

text.text:
First time visiting. Was craving a good burger. Ordered the one with the Mac & cheese and fried egg. I don't recall the name.

WARNING: Do not order this burger if you are wearing something fancy.

Why? Because this burger is an absolute mess in the best possible way. The beef is beefy, the onion ring does its level best to contain the Mac& Cheese, but it will ultimately fail, and when the dam breaks...

Don't get me wrong, you will LOVE everything about this burger... The pork belly and egg bring it to a 10... But there is a good chance you'll wear some of it.

We started with the onion rings, other onion rings wish they were these.

Only criticism, too many high top tables, I'm not a fan, so I took a booth.  Noticed a family with a young kid struggling to be comfortable. Ended up relocating when the few low tops opened up.

Went on a Saturday for lunch. I'm sure the dinner crowd may disagree... And that's okay.

Attention Foodies:  Had another epic adventure at the Twisted Cafe Tavern! ü•≥ Today, I indulged in Grilled Cheese Rolls with Tomato Soup for dipping‚Äîbecause why just eat when you can dunk? Also, devoured the legendary Cat Burger Smash Burger with those heavenly crispy onion rings! üòã

Doug, our amazing bartender, gave us the full culinary tour and beer 101.

I highly recommend bringing the family for a delightful escapade. The place has a chic, model vibe and is cleaner than your grandma's kitchen!

Drop by and say "Steve sent me" to get some exclusive water on the rocks! üíßü•É

The Lazy Cat was easily one of the best smash burgers I‚Äôve had in a while. One of the owners was running the bar and tending to all of the tables. He was very friendly, attentive and down-to-earth. Plenty of parking too on a Saturday afternoon. Highly recommend coming here if you have the chance!

cafes.name: Meows Corner
cafes.address: 21435 Epicerie Plaza Suite 115, Sterling, VA 20165, USA

text.text: A great place to get some cat time.  I happened here when my out of town relatives were visiting and they had a great time. All of the cats except one are rescues and up for adoption.  I see they have had 444 cats adopted since their inception.  Great cause and worth supporting‚Ä¶

Very nice, cute cat 'cafe'. As a former Foster for 4Paws, the rescue they supplies the cats and kittens for adoption, it was great to see where they go and even got to see some of our fosters! The place was clean and very cute. The staff were polite, knowledge, helpful, responsive, etc.

It's not really a cafe, but there were prepacked food and drinks. Prices are... Reasonable, understandably. It's a great business to get cats adopted.

Absolutely LOVED our visit to Meow's Corner! This cat cafe is super casual and chill, and it is really focused on the most important part--the cats. The environment was clean and there were plenty of places for the cats to play, hide, and sleep. The cats all seemed healthy and happy, and it was clear they were well taken care of. The staff member in charge was super sweet, and she seemed to know all of the cats' personalities and stories. And all of the cats are adoptable, so if you find one that you really click with, you can even take them home with you! Really a phenomenal experience; I'll definitely be back soon!!!

cafes.name: Crumbs & Whiskers | Kitten & Cat Cafe.
cafes.address: 3109 M St NW, Washington, DC 20007, USA

text.text: Really fantastic place that lets you hang out with adoptable cats in an awesome atmosphere! It‚Äôs especially nice for people like me who cannot adopt another animal myself but loves animal experiences and supporting rescue. The facility was clean, decorated beautifully, staff were really friendly and shared background stories on the cats and the kitty cats are all clearly well cared for. Visited Washington DC from Milwaukee, WI and I‚Äôm so glad we added this to our travel itinerary. The free Polaroid snapshot is such a nice touch and so unique (I‚Äôve been to 10 cat cafes and this is the only one I‚Äôve seen do this). I wish caffeine free tea options were available and would have preferred an hour long session for the price we paid but it‚Äôs for a fantastic cause so - 5/5 stars!

The sweetest cats I've ever encountered at any cat cafe. They were all happy and chillin. Some would approach you and others were so relaxed and happy they didn't mind at all when you approached them. A sweet cat in particular climbed right into my lap ‚ù§Ô∏èüòÅ we got a nice polaroid taken of me and my friend and now have that as a keepsake. From what I overheard, it sounds like all of the cats get adopted pretty quick. It feels good to support a place like this that does a lot of good things for cats and also is quite fun for me too!

Went for some kitty cuddle time and was not disappointed. The staff was friendly and kept a sharp eye on the cats. The cats were playful and energetic. We didn't get any food or drinks but they did have a menu. No shoes in the car hangout space so be sure to wear socks when you go. Also be patient, the cats operate on their own schedule.

Fuquay-Varina.name: Right Meow Cat Cafe
Fuquay-Varina.address: 913 S Main St, Fuquay-Varina, NC 27526, USA

text.text: Brought my daughter and friends here for her birthday.  Was an adorable place, super well done.  Decor was fabulous, cats were lovely and atmosphere is tranquil.  They also serve beverages.  I'm guessing we will be coming back!  Love the mission of the place for adopting cats and finding them forever homes!

Lovely and unique cafe! We made a last minute reservation online. As suggested, we arrived 10 minutes early to park and order our drinks (highly recommend arriving early!). The place was immaculate. It was very clean and free of odors. I‚Äôm not a cat person (my daughter is though- hence why we went!), and I fell in love with cats right there and then.
You can really tell they care about the safety and wellbeing on the cats. They‚Äôre all very clean and healthy. The place is calm and welcoming for both cats and humans. The cats have a large variety of places to go play, hide, sleep, etc., and cat toys are available in every room. We loved reading about each cat and getting to know them all. We were even given treats to feed the cats. The drinks were great, and my daughter tried the (‚Äúvery artistic‚Äù) red velvet cakepop. A friendly staff member kept coming in to check in and answer any questions. If we ever decide to adopt a cat, this would be the only place we would adopt from.

We love this place!! It has awesome drinks and booking time with the kitties is so special. You can tell the priority is the well being of the cats because they have so many amazing places throughout for them to hide and get out of reach if they are not feeling people-y. You will not find a cleaner establishment. (And if you didn't know, all the cats are up for adoption! Sadly we cannot due to allergies in the family but we love to go and support them).

cafes.name: Aristocat Cafe + Tea House
cafes.address: 111 N Liberty St, Harrisonburg, VA 22802, USA

text.text: I have been to this coffee shop two times and it has been an extremely delightful experience every time! Their matcha latte was one of the best I‚Äôve ever had, and their oat milk vanilla latte was equally delicious. Both times I‚Äôve went I also visited the cat lounge, you can tell the cats are very well taken care of and $15 for an hour is such a great price. Not only are the cats super cute but the money will help with their care! Will definitely be one of the coffee shops I‚Äôll be visiting regularly.

We went to celebrate my daughter's birthday and had the best time. Coffee and hot chocolate was delicious, with a ton of options for drinks and snacks. It was impeccably clean, including the cat area. Such a cool set up and the cats were adorable. Had a great chat with the owner and both she and the staff were warm and kind. We will definitely return. The best day with great memories made!
This was so fun! So clean (I have severe allergies) and it only affected me a little bit. The treats were delicious and the kitties was so great. Awesome service!

cafes.name: Cat's Cradle
cafes.address: 122 S Main St #101, Harrisonburg, VA 22801, USA

text.text: I love cats cradle so much! I have gotten all my babies from there, Wayne, Parenthesis and Banjo. They have a good variety of cats too. Wayne was a foster of ours when he was a foster fail, but Parenthesis and Banjo I found on their page. I love that they almost all have foster homes and get to live in a home while they wait to be adopted. Banjo was a senior and had quite a few issues which I knew was going to happen because I adopted him old‚Äîhe recently passed but I kept in touch with his old foster and always made sure she had an update too. They boys were both in great condition when I picked them up, the only thing is they did both have tape worm fragments I noticed after a few days with them. No big deal and treated with dewormer. I know with them being shelter/feral it happens and sometimes it takes multiple treatments to get fully rid of them but that was it! Obviously with being a cat owner, I bring them to the vet for yearly check-up‚Äôs and issues, but I also did take them after I adopted just to get blood ran, any meds needed and the full check-up and cats cradle were able to provide me with all their records they had and faxed them to Harrisonburg Animal Hospital as well. They also have roll over insurance‚Ä¶get it!! I used it both on Banjo and Parenthesis after I adopted for dewormer and checks and it was so worth it. Go get a kitty from cats cradle üíï

A must pop in for cat cuddles - Walking by as a stop on the way to the snow and spent a few minutes to contribute to the cause and got some cat cuddles in with Toby (tabby) and Zagreus (ginger) both males, and little cheddar (female).

Toby is a cuddly snuggle bug! a typical male tabby, who will chat to get your attention, was picked up no issue, sat on lap and wanted more

Zagreus is your typical male ginger, talkative and all for the love üíï he flopped and smooches into your hand

I only had 10 minutes and little cheddar was in need of a nap üòÑ
I want to thank you for the help with my kittens to get spay and neuter.I had a great experience with Anicira.I would have had to give them up.Again Thank  you so much. Socks and paws

My Husband and I have been here twice and we love it! It‚Äôs very clean, the staff are friendly and helpful and of course the cats and kittens are the best! You can tell that everyone who works there loves and cares for each of the kittens, it‚Äôs become our new favorite thing to do on the weekends! We can‚Äôt wait to come back! Also, as a GMU alumni/employee I LOVE that it‚Äôs so close to campus! 10/10!!

Super awesome and welcoming place, one of my new favorites to come and relax and recharge! Staff are super friendly and helpful, I asked them all sorts of things about the kitties. All of their cats are super sweet and would make great little house cats ü•∞ The kitten room was closed for cleaning so I‚Äôm definitely going to come back when it‚Äôs done. Recommending to everyone who loves cats or just needs an hour to relax with some cute babies.

I visited this place for the 1st time today and I enjoyed it so much. The employees and volunteers are all friendly and helpful, and you can tell they really care for the cats. The cats are adorable and most are very sweet. Some are a bit more standoffish, but they'll let you know if they don't want to be pet. There is enough space for people and cats to roam, and plenty of cats to play with. They provide a lot of toys for you to use, and the cats have a ton of trees and perches to nap on. The space is clean and doesn't smell, and you can tell the cats are well cared for. The price for a visit is reasonable in my opinion, and it helps them care for the cats. The only "negative" is how quickly the hour went by! I'll definitely visit again.

Greensboro.name: Crooked Tail Cat Cafe
Greensboro.address: 604 S Elm St, Greensboro, NC 27406, USA

text.text: Cute cute cute! My first time at a cat cafe, loved the cat themed drinks and the cat boba cups! All of the kitty cats were adorable, didn‚Äôt get the chance to play with them this time but definitely next time. Their gift shop has a bunch of cat themed items. Overall as a cat person I was over the moon!
This was such a cute place! It was fun learning about the cats and seeing their personalities.  It was very clean, and the cats seemed well taken care of. We would love to visit again one day!

We loved going here and the atmosphere was great!! The cats were playful and curious, very great friends.The drinks they had were great and no kitties knocked over any drinks. I can‚Äôt wait to come back here again!!

cafes.name: Lucky Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 1 W Main St, Salem, VA 24153, USA

text.text:
I‚Äôve came here a 1-2 years ago and the service was far superior! Today my husband and I ordered sushi first and then wanted ice cream. My husband and I waited in front of the gelato and no one even said we will be with you in a moment. 2 people literally saw us and I made contact multiple times. I stood patiently waiting and still nothing.

While waiting, I saw a gross bug on the side of the pistachio gelato and I would have taken a photo and I would have told the workers but no one came to see if we wanted anything. I‚Äôm mentioning the bug here so that they can take it out and it won‚Äôt end up in someone‚Äôs cup. I don‚Äôt think the bug is due to a lack of cleanliness because it‚Äôs clean. I think it probably flew inside when they opened the ice cream freezer and froze to death.

There were not even a lot of people in there so it‚Äôs not acceptable to me to just ignore customers. Especially considering we had just paid for food and bottled water.

Even as we walked out, there was no thank you or anything at all. The service is not good and I‚Äôm not sure if I will be back.
This shop is amazing! One of a kind, handmade gifts, the most delicious food you‚Äôve ever tasted, and to top it off fast and friendly service!
I was excited about the Mochi Donut but it was ok. Ice cream are different, in texture and flavors.

Chapel Hill.name: Cat Tales Cat Cafe
Chapel Hill.address: 431 W Franklin St, Chapel Hill, NC 27516, USA

text.text: Great place that takes care of cats - and allows people (for a fee) an hour to play with and pet the cats. There were about 9 of them when we went. You can buy drinks and get ice cream when you get in. Some cats wanted to be petted and would purr; others wanted to play and there were many toys. We spent the whole hour and it went by quickly. The cats are meant to be adopted.

Such a wonderful Cat Cafe and a great experience! The cats are obviously well cared for, the place was very clean, and it was a very relaxed atmosphere to visit the kitties. There were about seven of us in the location, and it never seemed crowded. The person helping at the front desk was very knowledgeable and patient with everyone, and they had a lot of cute things to shop for as well. Would definitely recommend this place!

An amazing place! Employees were so kind in helping me find a cat to adopt and very communicative during the transition period of bringing her home. The cafe itself is very clean and entertaining for cats and people with plenty of well cared for and well socialized cats. Cannot recommend this place enough!

Waldorf.name: Feline Felons Cat Cafe
Waldorf.address: 24 Industrial Park Dr #1, Waldorf, MD 20603, USA

text.text: The Humans, Peggy & Matt, are excellent conversationalists who clearly care very, very much about the wonderful feline population here who are awaiting their furever home! They are incredibly knowledgeable about all the cats who are temporary residents. The cats are AMAZING. Their space is extraordinary, their adoption options are wonderful! And there are a bunch of really great cat-themed things you can buy in the "meow-shop"

The best cat cafe place that cat lovers should check out,even best place for your kids !!! Great experience ! Great staffs ! We definitely come back soon . My kids enjoyed their time there with all lovely kittens, they want to come back to see cat lounge .And we love their cat gifts shop with affordable prices .They have kittens and cats for adoption (the fee to me is much better than any places I used to ).

If you love cats this is a place you must see. The workers are great and very helpful. Tons of kitty's that ate very loving all sizes and ages. Very clean and well kept... and yes we brought one home. We will be going back to just visit all the kitty's.  But really if you love cats it's 100% worth checking out.

cafes.name: Ollie Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 219 W Main St, Luray, VA 22835, USA

text.text: Honestly, giving this place even 1 star feels too generous. We ordered the mahi sandwich, and the fish smelled off while the bread was way over-fried. The onion rings tasted like they were cooked in old, overused oil, and the hot dog was awful‚Äîseriously, you could get a better one from a food truck. To top it off, the bathroom was clogged and gross. You could tell from the food that the grill hadn‚Äôt been cleaned properly. The only saving grace was the waiter, who did a great job, but everything else was just bad. The restaurant is called Cat Cafe, but honestly, I don‚Äôt think even cats would eat the food here. We left most of it on the table. Definitely won‚Äôt be back, and if you‚Äôre thinking of visiting, do yourself a favor and read the reviews first. Total waste of money and time.

We arrived around 7pm but it took us closer to 8pm to get our food.  We found the service peculiar.  We first had a drink server who struggled with retention of our drink order.  When he didn't return for awhile, we asked for a service.  A new woman arrived and then immediately said, 'it wasn't my fault.'  She then guessed which ones of us would be the difficult orders.  The food service was slow. The owner chatted us up while we waited for our food, telling us about her rescues.  She assured us that we could stay as long as we needed, getting dessert or after-dinner drinks.  When the time came to make the decision the waitress quickly told us the kitchen was closed.  She walked it back when I told her what the owner said, but it clearly would have been a hassle for her to do so.  The food was good.  It filled the stomach and was above average, but we might see what else we could find in the future or try to come at a less busy time.

I have never been so pleasantly surprised & impressed by a restaurant/cafe. The atmosphere was uplifting and funny, the customer service was phenomenal and it's food was chefs kiss amazing! We will now drive 45 mins on the regular just to come here! Thank you Ed and Laura, you guys made this a great experience!

cafes.name: With Love Cat & Theia - Artisan Bakery & Cafe
cafes.address: 4711 W Broad St, Richmond, VA 23230, USA

text.text: Absolutely delightful and delicious sandwiches and pastries! My fianc√© and I ordered the West End and Hyperion sandwiches on scallion pancakes. Everything was fresh and well seasoned! We also tried an amazing blackcurrant pastry and adored the fun flavor combinations. Appreciated the sustainable bamboo silverware, too! The storefront is mostly set up for delivery services, so I‚Äôd consider ordering for pickup next time! We can‚Äôt wait to come back and continue exploring Cat and Theia‚Äôs exciting menu!

Have been many times since they reopened after the pandemic. We love the lentil burger and fries as well as the nachos with roasted veggies. Salads and soups are quite good as well. Highly recommend Stray Cat as a casual, warm neighborhood restaurant!
Food here is pretty good. The bar tender was super nice and great service. I like how all the sandwiches can be done in a burger, chicken, and veggie.

Very good & attentive staff. Menu has a good variety. The ambiance is nice and the walls are covered with colorful "Cat-art".  All items on the menu are even named keeping felines in mind. Great place to meet up for a low key appetizing meal. There's a full bar also. A fraction of the $$ the restaurant makes, goes towards rescuing & caring for stray cats. The restaurant group also organizes several adoption events throughout the year. Tag->Also check out a sister restaurant: "Stray Dog Cafe"üëçüëç
